Calls a function with a reference to the contained value if [`Err`].

Returns the original result.

# Examples

```
use std::{fs, io};

fn read() -> io::Result<String> {
    fs::read_to_string("address.txt")
        .inspect_err(|e| eprintln!("failed to read file: {e}"))
}
